title: High-school football | MLS roundup: Redmen's late TD lifts Whitehall over London
text:
Rams Quarterback DeShante Vaughn had 149 yards passing and led Whitehall with 103 yards rushing. Taquan Williams had a fumble recovery and an interception. 
Bexley 52, Millersport 0 
Jack Nagle scored on a kickoff return, fumble return and a 41-yard pass, and Bexley (6-1) rolled past visiting Millersport (2-5) in a nonleague game. Sean Early rushed for 100 yards on four carries and scored on a 48-yard run. Rico Truss also had two rushing TDs for the Lions. 
Grandview 35, West Jefferson 6 
Andre Readey threw four TDs and added another rushing, and Grandview (6-1, 3-1) defeated visiting West Jefferson (2-5, 1-2) in the MSL Ohio. Readey completed 7 of 12 passes for 176 yards and had scoring throws of 26, 15, 98 and 16 yards. He also rushed for 156 yards on 11 carries and scored on a 30-yard run. Hudson Jump caught two passes for 101 yards, and James Lachey caught two TD passes for Grandview. 
Bloom-Carroll 30, Amanda-Clearcreek 13 
Dylan Jude had two rushing TDs, and Bloom-Carroll (5-2, 3-1) scored all its points in the first half to defeat host Amanda-Clearcreek (1-6, 0-4) in the MSL Buckeye. 
Logan Elm 23, Circleville 21 
Jakob Sheumaker caught a 20-yard TD pass from Marcus Paul with 34 seconds remaining, and Logan Elm (6-1, 4-0) rallied from a 14-point deficit to beat host Circleville (4-3, 1-3) in the MSL Buckeye. Paul gained 161 yards rushing on 33 carries and accounted for three TDs. Michael Camp got Circleville into scoring position with three seconds remaining, but the Tigers missed a 45-yard field goal. Camp completed 23 of 34 passes for 294 yards and two TDs. 
Hamilton Township 55, Fairfield Union 13 
Trey Johnson scored four touchdowns to lead Hamilton Township (5-2, 3-1) past visiting Fairfield Union (3-4, 1-3) in the MSL Buckeye. Johnson, who finished with 132 yards rushing, scored his third TD on the ground from 68 yards to give the Rangers a 34-0 lead. He added a 78-yard kickoff return for a touchdown late in the second quarter. 
Teays Valley 59, Liberty Union 0 
Quarterback Drew Pennington rushed for four TDs in the first half, and Teays Valley (5-2, 4-0) stayed atop the MSL Cardinal by routing visiting Liberty Union (1-6, 0-4). Pennington finished with 101 yards rushing. John Walkowicz scored three TDs, including a 90-yard kickoff return to start the second half. 
Harvest Prep 39, Berne Union 14 
Daniel Bangura had 167 yards rushing and totaled three touchdowns as Harvest Prep (5-2, 3-0) ran away with an MSL Cardinal win over host Berne Union (2-5, 1-3). Bangura helped give the Warriors a 21-0 lead with TD runs of 20 and 23 in the first quarter. After the Rockets cut their deficit to seven points, quarterback Rodney Meyer scored on two short runs in the third and threw a 20-yard TD pass to Bangura in the fourth. 
Fairfield Christian 27, Grove City Christian 0 
Joshua Heeter ran for 92 yards and a first-quarter touchdown to help Fairfield Christian (3-4, 2-1) shut out host Grove City Christian (0-7, 0-4) in the MSL Cardinal. The Knights outgained the Eagles by just 2 yards - 234-232 - but Fairfield Christianâ€™s defense forced three turnovers, including a fumble Bobby Leeper returned 64 yards for a TD.
